{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a70417cc3fb48d68510", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d70bd9948bc1b21da2b1f"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6ebac"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "648b5a3a0d9d0b909f7b6491", "title": "JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "<p>Given below are two statements: one is labelled as <strong>Assertion A</strong> and the other is labelled as <strong>Reason R</strong>.</p><p><strong>Assertion A</strong> : The energy required to form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Mg</mi></math>&nbsp;is much higher than that required to produce&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p><p><strong>Reason R</strong>:<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;is small ion and carry more charge than&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math></p><p>In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below.</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "mAMUg", "text": "Both <strong>A</strong>&nbsp;and <b>R</b>&nbsp;are true but <b>R</b>&nbsp;is <strong>NOT</strong> the correct explanation of <b>A</b>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "xQGYT", "text": "<strong>A</strong> is true but <strong>R</strong> is false", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "Q2ypT", "text": "<strong>A</strong> is false but <strong>R</strong> is true", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "x86bQ", "text": "Both <strong>A</strong> and <strong>R</strong> are true and <strong>R</strong> is the correct explanation of <strong>A</strong>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Mg have <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math> electrons in valance shell and after donation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></math>electrons it converts into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;ion and attains inert gas configuration,&nbsp;now to ionize one more electron from inert gas configuration is very difficult,&nbsp;hence it is easy to ionize <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Mg</mi></math> to<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>IE</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> is always greater than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>IE</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> because on removal of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></math>, size decreases and effective nuclear charge increases.So Assertion is correct.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math> is a smaller ion than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math> and has a greater charge density. This means that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math> has a stronger attraction to its electrons than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math> and requires more energy to remove an electron from it. So reason is also correct.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ53104136", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "Easy Ques (Board Level)", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["615f0cf69476412f48314dac", "616057040283de43c87e3e16", "61bb58281213731910ea0b71", "6160579d0283de43c87e3e1f", "61964f94a5a526011886801e", "61c055f6e8ce0dc8a5c62d34", "61a8a2cce8ce0dc8a5c62d2e", "6160577e0283de43c87e3e1c", "616057210283de43c87e3e19", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352c", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd8", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7e", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625c", "61964ff3a5a5260118868022", "64d50c263df7f4a7f3017f70", "66b79b89d4b564dfab4f94d0", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc12", "67fa602f4468eb1307ceb0ae", "6807d350647479b8e869647a"], "cpyqbChapters": ["6160247b7b82dd1366035a18", "6160247cf3a1c434932a4a88", "6160247ab6649a28dbb20abf", "61bb822bb4fb582ae09d2bd9", "61964c9bd2cad6ca730c35eb", "61964c9b440022dde741c32c", "6160247be77fd39da8bbabec", "61602479b6bda5480d7f73bd", "61e7bd80be29bf9b0cc9a13e", "61c089bab09d88093a4a36a4", "629109db0f9ec90f29d91e43", "629f38feee42062b717eb566", "6296211727931cb3b88eccdd", "629f3a84643e3427b020772e", "64eb06ea3118f713ecfef22e", "66d5853ea75f05ee8564f58f", "67921db51d5b5072da5e9d42", "67fdff5a378e1624ea7b6a8f", "68091ffe3a10446a207fdd13"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}